    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "targeted_sweep9_long_duration_2016",
    "description": "Long-duration 2016-block retarget run to observe what happens when the minority chain (v27 at 25% hashrate) reaches its first difficulty adjustment.\nThis is a prerequisite to targeted_sweep10 (economic threshold at 2016-block). The key question: does the \"stuck contested\" state found in sweep8 (v27 ~50%, v26 ~36% hashrate at t=7200s) resolve into a decisive winner once v27's difficulty drops ~75%? The answer determines what duration to use for all subsequent 2016-block sweeps.\nTiming estimate for first v27 retarget:\n  - v27 starts at 25% hashrate \u2192 1 block per ~8s\n  - Neutral pools migrate to v27 early \u2192 hashrate rises to ~50.5% \u2192 1 block per ~4s\n  - Phase 1 (~3000s at ~30% avg hashrate): ~450 v27 blocks\n  - Phase 2 (remaining at ~50.5% hashrate): ~1566 more blocks needed at ~4s each\n  - Estimated first v27 retarget: t \u2248 9,000\u201311,000s\n  - Running to 20,000s captures the retarget and ~9,000s of post-retarget dynamics\n\necon=0.70 chosen because:\n  - Clean contested result in sweep8 (no ambiguity)\n  - Well inside the contested zone \u2014 not near the threshold\n  - If the cascade completes post-retarget at econ=0.70, it likely completes\n    everywhere below 0.82; if it doesn't, the threshold sweep can use 7200s safely\n\nExpected observations:\n  - t=0\u20137200s:    identical to sweep8 (neutral pools migrate, committed v26 holds)\n  - t\u22489000\u201311000s: v27 difficulty drops ~50-60% (partial drop since hashrate only\n                  fell to ~50%, not 25%)\n  - t>11000s:     profit spike arrives \u2014 do committed v26 pools switch?\n                  YES \u2192 cascade completes, v27 dominant\n                  NO  \u2192 stuck contested persists, 7200s is valid for threshold sweep\n\nIMPORTANT: Run with --retarget-interval 2016 and --duration 20000\n",
